# Phase 1: Analyze the Fix

This is a patch for InstCombine:

[InstCombine] Fold zext into de-interleaving (factor=2) instructions
Given the following de-interleaving shufflevectors and the consuming zexts:
```
%f0 = shufflevector <8 x i32> %v, <4 x i32> <i32 0, i32 2, i32 4, i32 6>
%f1 = shufflevector <8 x i32> %v, <4 x i32> <i32 1, i32 3, i32 5, i32 7>
%z0 = zext <4 x i32> %f0 to <4 x i64>
%z1 = zext <4 x i32> %f1 to <4 x i64>
```
We can actually bitcast the input value, `%v`, first into a vector type with double the element size but half the vector length, before replacing zexts with simple arithmetics on this new bitcast:
```
%bc = bitcast <8 x i32> %v to <4 x i64>
%z0 = and <4 x i64> %bc, splat (i64 4294967295)
%z1 = lshr <4 x i64> %bc, splat (i64 32)
```
This transformation is almost always benefitial as shufflevector is generally more expensive than normal arithmetics.

-----
Found this pattern in real benchmarks. This pattern is similar to #192121 except it's widening not narrowing the deinterleaved fields. I actually tried to consolidate these two patches but I found that #192121 is almost only benefit on larger code region shown in that patch, while this patch can optimize simpler pattern, zext + shufflevector / deinterleave2.
